  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water Supply and Sanitation Sector Programme had the overall objective of contributing to poverty reduction in Ghana by improving access to safe drinking water and sanitation in 52 rural areas. Access to water and sanitation has also a demonstrable positive impact on the overall health conditions/status in rural areas. 

The program sought to actively support the decentralization process in Ghana and donor harmonization. Beside the Danish Embassy, the Programme Steering Committee members consisted of members from civil society, other development partners that support water and sanitation sector in Ghana (Holland &amp; England) and the Ministry responsible for decentralization and environment. The Committee was headed by Ministry of Water.</narrative>
  </description>
